 Ronald Pearson and his wife Miriam met at an evening dance while he was serving in the RAF police and she the Auxiliary Territorial Service during the Second World War .
They married in 1943 and settled in Broughton near Chester , welcoming their daughter two years after celebrating VE day .
After almost 72 years together , Mrs Pearson , 95 , died last month .
Their marriage was described as ` the greatest true love story .